<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>AFS0094</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">              </span></p><div style="border-bottom-color:#4f81bd; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:1pt; clear:both; margin:0pt 0pt 15pt 18pt"><p style="margin:0pt; padding-bottom:15pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.25pt">AFS0094</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; padding-bottom:15pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.25pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; padding-bottom:4pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.25pt">Written Evidence from </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.25pt">Suffolk Coalition Opposing Free Schools (SCOFS)</span></p></div><h1 style="margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">Sum</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">mary</span></h1><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">A number of small but expensive</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> mainstream</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> free schools have opened in Suffolk. The exact costs were never adequately analysed.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The new</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> small</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> mainstream free schools have brought no innovation and no improved choice of education to Suffolk.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The process for opening </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">new free schools in Suffolk app</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ears to have been entirely opaque and one-sided in favour of free-school proposers.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The impact, including cost, on the local authority appears to have been ignored.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">What little public debate there has been with what little public information there is </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">has</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> been subject to one-sided intimidation and harassment.</span></li></ol><h1 style="margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">Background</span></h1><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Suffolk Coalition Opposing Free Schools (SCOFS) was created to bring together parents and teachers concerned by the damaging</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> effects of</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> attempts</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> by</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> vocal minority parent groups across Suff</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">olk to create small secondary free schools on the sites of closing middle schools.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Suffolk County Council (SCC)’s School Organisation Review (SOR) </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">planned to replace</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">remaining </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">3-tier school structure</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">s in Suffolk with </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">2-tier structure</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">, and close middl</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">e schools.</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> This created both empty middle school sites and a simultaneous transfer of three year groups from middle to secondary school.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">SCOFS felt that small free schools with a narrow curriculum could not provide an adequate education for the majority o</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">f children and, in a county which already has excess secondary school places, would be harmful to larger schools nearby, which could, resulting in a po</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">orer education for all children, as well as wasting large amounts of public money.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Since then, SCOFS con</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">cerns over free schools have expanded to include the apparently complete lack of transparency and accountability in setting up free schools, even where there is no demand.</span></li></ol><h1 style="margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">12.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">Costs</span></h1><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The total cost of opening small free schools in Suffolk is obfuscated by sever</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">al factors.</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The total cost is made up of several different items split between SCC and the Department for Education (DfE) that are difficult to collate and report together.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The Department for Education (DfE) and free school proposers are slow and </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">uncooperative in sharing</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> financial</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> information, even in the face of Freedom of Information Act (FoIA) requests. Several FOIA requests relating to cost have been delayed or refused.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Key information</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> about free school proposals</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> held by non-public bodies, such as </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Internationella Engelska Skolan</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> (IES) and the Seckford Foundation, cannot be reached using FoIA.</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> By the time the school is set up as a public body, it is too late.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">As far as we know, the full cost of opening the school </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">to both SCC and DfE combined, has never been calculated or documented. It seems impossible, therefore than anyone could have made a meaningful assessment of value for money.</span></li></ol><h1 style="margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">17.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">Land and Buildings</span></h1><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Were it not for free schools, </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">SCC would either dispose of surpl</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">us middle school sites or reuse them for other public purposes. These are valuable sites and the cost to SCC i</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">n </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">not reusing or disposing </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">of them </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">is large</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Costs incurred by DfE in creating new free schools include the capital inve</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">stment in converting, </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">upg</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">rading</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> and equipping</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> existing buildings in Clare</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> (Stour Valley)</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">, Brandon (IES</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> Breckland</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">), Carlton Colville (Beccles), Saxmundham, and Ixworth. If Beccles Free School ever moves to Beccles, there will be a second round of cost to convert the Beccles site.</span></li></ol><h1 style="margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">20.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">R</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">evenue Costs</span></h1><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">In addition to this there is start-up funding, pre-opening funding and diseconomy funding while the school does not have a full set of years in school.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="22" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Much of this funding appears to be scaled to the intended rather than actual size of the s</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">chool, so the funding is not only for </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">theoretical </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">future pupil numbers who are not yet at the school, but also, when the school turns out to be much smaller than planned, fictional pupil numbers who will never ever be at the school.</span></li></ol><h1 style="margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">23.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">Transport</span></h1><ol start="24" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">A major cost </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">to SCC is the provision of home-to-school transport. The serious impact of free schools on home-to-school transport costs and planning appears to have been ignored or underestimated.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="25" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Prior to the creation of free schools, SCC operated a patchwork of catch</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ment areas for secondary schools. Free transport was offered to either the nearest or catchment school, which was usually the same</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> school</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="26" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Following the creation of f</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ree schools, this policy became unworkable. Firstly free schools do not have enough capac</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ity for all the pupils nearest to them and secondly, their </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">narrow curriculum is not suitable for all pupils.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="27" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Following lobbying by local politicians, bullying by the DfE and a public consultation, we now have the ridiculous situation that small free schoo</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ls in </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Clare (Stour Valley), Brandon (IES Breckland), Carlton Colville (Beccles), and Saxmundham </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">now have free transport covering a an equal or larger area than nearby full-size schools in Haverhill, Sudbury, Mildenhall, Beccles, and Leiston.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="28" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The new polic</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">y is justified on grounds of choice and competition, but, in fact, much more effective choice and competition could have been generated by offering transport to two nearby full-size schools and not creating a small free school.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="29" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Graham Watson, Director of </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">the Seckford Foundation, speaking at an Ixworth Free School meeting on Thursday 15 November 2012 in response to a question from the audience about home-to-school transport said the following:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="30" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">“Home-to-school transport is something that’s incredibly dear </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">to my heart.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="31" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">“I’ve been asked by the DfE to be a member of a team to help look at home-to-school transport in rural counties. Because Seckford has got a problem and I suspect other free schools that open up in a rural county will have the same thing.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="32" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">“At</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> the moment we’re not being treated fairly. And therefore the foundation, the thing the foundation is doing, is making sure that any pupil that wants to come to “Beccles or Saxmundham can come, regardless of transport issues, because actually you’re choosi</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ng education, you’re not choosing the practicalities.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="33" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">“We think that, by the time we get to 2014, when this school opens, the home-to-school transport landscape in this county will have changed.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="34" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">“We are discussing with the Department for Education that w</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">e will run our own transport system. As Woodbridge School we currently run eight or nine bus routes. We know exactly how to do it. We are qualified to do it. We know how to get young people to and from school at different times.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="35" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">“One of the things I grew </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">up in a rural situation and, of course, I was lucky that my parents could take me at different times to do different things, but not all children are that fortunate, so that one of the things that Rob and I are very keen is that transport policy means that</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> every child is included, whatever they want to do, and not excluded.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="36" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">“Anyway, the foundation will work with the school to make that happen.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="37" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">“As I said, nationally, I’m involved in trying to change the home-to-school transport policy, and it will be done</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> by 2014.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="38" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">It is hard to see any justification for Watson’s claim not to be treated fairly given that Seckford’s small schools have larger catchment areas than full-size ones.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="39" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">It is not clear who set up the DfE team Watson refers to, what its remit is or </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">how its members were selected.</span></li></ol><h1 style="margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">40.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">Size and Choice</span></h1><ol start="41" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Prior to free schools, SCC, as part of SOR, had a target size for secondary schools of 1,200 with a range of 900 to 1,500. This is a full-size school.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="42" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Schools of this size are able to, and do, offer a range o</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">f academic and vocational courses to suit everyone from the most to the least able.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="43" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Not only are small free schools with a maximum size of 540 and typical size of 100 to 300 not able to </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">offer as full, if any,</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> choice of </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">courses, or</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> a sufficient range to co</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ver all abilities, but they draw pupils away from nearby full-size schools thus </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">damaging</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> the existing choice</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> of courses</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> there too.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="44" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">This impact does not appear to have been taken into account when opening free schools in Suffolk.</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> Choice of school seems to have been mistaken for choice of education.</span></li></ol><h1 style="margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">45.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">Transparency</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">in the Opening Process</span></h1><ol start="46" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The applications to open free schools have not been published and have therefore not </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">been subject to public scrutiny or verification.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="47" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Impact assessm</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ents have not been published promptly, and where they have later been made public, often show a</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> negative impact, which appears to have been</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> ignored.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="48" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Impact assessment for Stour Valley</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">, opened Sep 2011</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">, published Oct 2013</span></li><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/free-schools-that-opened-in-2011"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/free-schools-that-opened-in-2011</span></a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="50" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Impact assessment for Beccles, </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">IES Breckland and Saxmundham, opened Sep 2012, published Oct 2013</span></li><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/free-schools-that-opened-in-2012"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/free-schools-that-opened-in-2012</span></a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="52" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Public consultations are carried out </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">and consultation reports are written </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">by the propo</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ers </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">themselves, or their consultants, and appear to be </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">perfunctory in nature, skewed in favour of the free school, and again are</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> published long after the </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">opening</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> by the proposers, rather than the DfE.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="53" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The Beccles Free School consultation ignored an overwh</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">elming majority</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> of responses</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> against the school opening.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="54" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Ofsted pre-opening reports </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">were also only published after a significant delay.</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> Seckford claimed</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> in an advertisement</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> that Beccles Free School passed “with flying colours”</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">, subsequent publication show</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ed that Ofsted had raised concerns and demanded remediations.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="55" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Ofsted reports for for Stour Valley, opened Sep 2011, published Jan 2012</span></li><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/free-schools-pre-registration-inspection"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.gov.uk/gove</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">rnment/publications/free-schools-pre-registration-inspection</span></a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="57" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Ofsted reports for Beccles, IES Breckland and Saxmundham, opened Sep 2012, published Dec 2012</span></li><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ofsted-pre-registration-advice-notes-2012"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ofsted-pre-registration-advice-notes-2012</span></a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="59" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">DfE makes its decisions solely on the basis of information </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">provided in secret by proposers, but DfE does not have local knowledge of Suffolk.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="60" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Meanwhile, people in </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Suffolk, especially professionals, do not either see the proposals or get to comment on them in a way that could guide the DfE to better decisions.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="61" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">We know that there has been substantial lobbying behind the scenes by councillors and MPs, but it is not cl</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ear how much influence this had on decision making.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="62" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The whole decision-making process appears to be opaque and ill-informed.</span></li></ol><h1 style="margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">63.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">Secrecy </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">with both DfE and Parents</span></h1><ol start="64" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">With the notable exception of Stour Valley, free schools in Suffolk have not been opened by or u</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">nder the control of parents.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="65" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The parent groups in Brandon, Beccles, Saxmundham and Ixworth proved unable to set up their own schools. These groups were somehow introduced to IES and Seckford Foundation who effectively took them over and replaced any propo</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">sals with their own.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="66" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">IES Breckland is now run from Sweden by IES, with the Sabres Educational Trust acting purely as a passive conduit.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="67" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Seckford Free Schools in Beccles, Saxmundham</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">, potentially,</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> Ixworth are run from Woodbridge by the Seckford Foundation </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">using a centralised governance structure </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">with very little parental involvement</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> or control</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="68" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">What is left of the parent groups is now reduced to recruitment and cheerleading. It is not clear if par</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ent groups ever saw the Seckford proposal to DfE in full, as Seckford, not the parent group, were the proposers.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="69" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Since these takeovers, the parent groups and their members have not spoken publicly about anything. The proposers handle all the publicity.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="70" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">hus DfE does not know what IES and Seckford have said to parents, and parents don’t know what IES and Seckford have said to DfE. </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">There is no way o</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">f knowing if these are the same.</span></li></ol><h1 style="margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">71.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">Recruitment</span></h1><ol start="72" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Seckford told DfE they had large demand, but, in reality, they ha</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ve struggled to turn that alleged demand into recruitment after being approved.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="73" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Seckford and IES told parents that they would recruit high quality staff, but, in reality, both have had difficulty recruiting and retaining head teachers and heads of key </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">subjects including English and Maths.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="74" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The head teacher</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">, Sherry Zand,</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> and heads of English and Maths all recently left IES Breckland.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="75" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The original head teacher recruited for Saxmundham pulled out immediately and a replacement wasn’t recruited until a year</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> after opening.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="76" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The head of English at Saxmundham was recruited shortly after her abrupt departure from Thetford Academy and left equally abruptly after one term at Saxmundham.</span></li></ol><h1 style="margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">77.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">Misleading Advertising</span></h1><ol start="78" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The Advertising Standards Authority (ASA) for misleadin</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">g advertising has repeatedly censured Seckford.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="79" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The head teacher at Beccles</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">, John Lucas,</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> claimed </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">in an advert </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">to have been “Director of Learning for Cambridgeshire”</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Such a post</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> exists, but Lucas has never held it.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="80" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Since Lucas makes the same claim on the</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> professional networking site, LinkedIn, it is quite likely that Lucas lied to Seckford and Seckford didn’t check before repeating this false claim.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="81" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Seckford claimed Beccles was an “outstanding school” despite never having been fully inspected by Ofsted.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="82" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Seckford claimed Beccles passed its Ofsted pre-opening inspection “with flying colours” even though we now know that Ofsted raised several significant concerns to be remediated.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="83" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">It is on the basis of such false claims that Seckford is recruiting pupils t</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">o Beccles, Saxmundham and Ixworth schools.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="84" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The ASA adjudication can be found here:</span></li><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><a href="http://www.asa.org.uk/Rulings/Adjudications/2013/1/The-Seckford-Foundation-Free-Schools-Trust/SHP_ADJ_208824.aspx"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.asa.org.uk/Rulings/Adjudications/2</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">013/1/The-Seckford-Foundation-Free-Schools-Trust/SHP_ADJ_208824.aspx</span></a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="86" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Cambridge</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">shire Children, Families and Adults Directorate structure, including the Director for Learning, can be found here:</span></li><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><a href="http://www.cambridgeshire.gov.uk/council/council-structure.htm#1"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.cambridgeshire.gov.uk/council/council-structure.htm#1</span></a></li></ol><h1 style="margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">88.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">Harassment and Intimidation</span></h1><ol start="89" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Michael Gove, Seckford’s Graham Watson and other </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">proposers of free schools</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> have claimed that they have been </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">or might be subject to harassment and intimidation</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> as a consequence of proposing a free school and used this </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">as a reason for withholding and delay</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ing publication of applications and other documents.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="90" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">We can find no</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> evidenc</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">e to support this claim in Suffolk.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="91" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Meanwhile, however, the converse is definitely true. Parents, governors and teachers have been the subject of harassment and intimidation to maintain secrecy and silence opposition.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="92" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Graham Watson and Stephen Larder spe</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">cifically instructed members of the Ixworth parent group not to discuss or disclose any information publicly or privately except as directed by them.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="93" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">SCC </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">councillors and officers have repeatedly pressured schools in the Thurston area, </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">which</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> would be direc</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">tly affected, and their staff</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">, both verbally and in writing</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> not to comment </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">negatively </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">on the Ixworth free school proposal.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="94" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Parents and councillors linked to free school proposals have made spurious complaints about opponents to their schools in an attemp</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">t to silence them.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="95" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Similar complaints have also been made anonymously.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="96" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Seckford has made legal threats against </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">opponents to silence them, rather than challenge the facts openly.</span></li></ol><h1 style="margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">97.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">Recommendations</span></h1><ol start="98" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The process for opening free schools should be made much mor</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">e r</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">igorous, robust and tran</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">sparent, with a clear timetable, </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">responsibility and </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">accountability</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="99" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">All documents relating to an application and the application process, including impact assessments, consultation reports and Ofsted pre-opening checks should be</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> published promptly and in full.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="100" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">It should be made clear to free school proposers at the beginning of the application process that they are applying to create an accountable public body and that that accountability starts with the application itself.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="101" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> full costs of opening a free school, to DfE, local authorities and nearby schools, should be fully analysed, published and included in decision making.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="102" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Start-up funding for new free schools should be more closely linked to ac</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">tual rather than planned dema</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">nd, including claw-back provisions where appropriate.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="103" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">A clear assessment of the value of the proposed free school against existing provision should be made before opening.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="104" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Choice of education should be given high</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">er weight than choice of school in </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">deciding free school applications.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="105" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Local authorities and local schools should be invited to comment on free school proposals that affect them.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="106" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The consultation process should be conducted entirely independently of the free school proposers by a neutral t</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">hird party reporting directly t</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">o DfE or the secretary of state, with the report published promptly.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="107" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Free schools should be monitored more closely after opening to check that progress on key implementation targets, including the recruitment of staff and pu</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">pils, are being met.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="108" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Martin Campbell on behalf of Suffolk Coalition Opposing Free Schools (SCOFS)</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">     </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">              </span></p></div></body></html>